# GitHub workflow

All work uses [GitHub issues](https://github.com/Gitter499/cyclosim/issues) and pull requests.

## Branching

- **`dev`**: integration hub; merge feature work here quickly.
- **`main`**: stable releases; merge from `dev` via PR **only when CI passes**.
- Feature branches: `feat/issue-N-short-name` or `chore/...` from latest `dev`.

## Development velocity

- **Do not block on CI** to land work on `dev`. Run `cargo test` locally; push and merge.
- **CI gate applies to `main` only** (branch protection requires `test`).
- Open PRs to `dev` for review history, or merge feature branches directly when iterating fast.

## Pull requests

- One milestone or focused change per PR when practical.
- Title references the issue: `feat: M5 workout engine (#10)`.
- Body includes `Closes #N` when the PR completes an issue.
- Granular commits on the branch.
- **No AI tool branding** in titles, bodies, or commits (see [no-tool-branding.mdc](no-tool-branding.mdc)).

